    "128535695": {
      "title": "High resolution spectroradiometry: Spectral reflectance of field bean leaves infected by Botrytis fabae",
      "abstract": "Abstract The spectral leaf reflectance properties of field bean ( Vicia faba ) infected by the fungus Botrytis fabae were investigated over the wavelength range 400–1100 nm. The percentage of leaf surface affected by lesions was estimated, as well as fresh weight, and content of photosynthetic pigments per unit leaf area. Measurements of photosynthetic rates and stomatal conductance were conducted on groups of diseased and control leaves. Chlorophyll b content increased significantly as the proportion of leaf surface infected increased, but no statistically significant change was observed in chlorophyll a content. Rates of leaf photosynthesis were reduced significantly compared to healthy leaves even at low levels of infection ("
